Police at Colesberg have arrested two men after they were found in possession of a suspected stolen car and a large amount of cash, Northern Cape police said on Saturday. Swift police action and vigilance on Thursday led to the arrest of the two men after they were spotted in a suspected stolen car at an eatery outlet in Colesberg on the N1, the South African Police Service (SAPS) said in a statement posted on the Arrive Alive website. The suspects were driving a white BMW with GP (Gauteng) registration number plates. Upon further investigation and searching the vehicle an undisclosed amount of cash was found hidden in a secret compartment inside the vehicle. The suspects could not give a satisfactory account for the money during questioning. The suspects are detained and the investigation is continuing to determine the source of the money, the SAPS statement said. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.